HEADWORD: Unspecialized
<hw>Un*spe"cial*ized</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Not
specialized; specifically <fld>(Biol.)</fld>, not adapted, or set apart,
for any particular purpose or function; <as>as, an
<ex>unspecialized</ex> unicellular organism</as>.</def> <rj><au>W. K.
Brooks.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

